      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Conclusion: EDTA forms the more stable Fe3+ complex. At 25 °C and I = 0.10 M, the Fe3+–EDTA complex is ~9.2 log units more stable than Fe3+–NTA (≈1.6×10^9 times). EDTA’s higher denticity (hexadentate) compared with NTA (tridentate) provides a stronger chelate effect, consistent with these much larger stability constants; increasing ionic strength modestly lowers the apparent log β for both ligands.",
